RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman made a phone call to Singaporean Prime Minister Lee Hsien Loong, Saudi Press Agency reported on Tuesday.
During the call, they discussed relations between the two countries in various fields and ways of developing them.
The two sides also reviewed “promising opportunities within the work of the Saudi-Singapore Joint Committee,” SPA said. Spoke with Saudi Crown Prince Mohammad Bin Salman over the phone tdy. I expressed hope for our Haj quota to be increased when it resumes for intl pilgrims. Look fwd to meeting in person again as our countries mark 45yrs of diplomatic ties this yr. ​– LHL https://t.co/0vdrXpoI3A pic.twitter.com/m918gZemT4 — leehsienloong (@leehsienloong) February 8, 2022 